libcint
=======

version 1.0
2013-01-15


What is libcint
---------------

libcint is an open source library for computation of Gaussian type
integrals.  It provides C/Fortran function to evaluate one-electron /
two-electron integrals with Cartesian / spheric / spinor Gaussian type
functions.


Features
--------

* one electron integrals
  - plain integrals such as overlap, kinetic integrals
  - nuclear attraction
  - nuclear attraction due to Gaussian nuclear model
* two electron integrals
  - Coulomb repulsion
  - Gaunt interaction
* Cartesian GTO
  - integrals for 6d, 10f, 15g Gaussian functions
* spheric GTO 
  - integrals for 5d, 7f, 9g Gaussian functions
* spinor GTO 
  - integrals for J-adapted spinor Gaussian functions
* common lisp script to automatically generate C code
* thread safe


Getting libcint
---------------

The latest version is available from:

    git clone http://github.com/xxxxxxxxx


Installation
------------

* Prerequisites
  - BLAS library
  - Python version 2.5 or higher (optional, for make check)
  - common lisp / SBCL (optional, for common lisp script)

* Build libcint via
    mkdir build; cd build
    ../configure <options>
    make
    make check  # optional
    make install

* Use Intel MKL as BLAS library
  - MKL version 10.2 or older
    ./configure --with-blas="-Wl,--start-group -L$MKLROOT/lib/intel64 -lmkl_intel_lp64 \
        -lmkl_sequential -lmkl_core -lmkl_mc -lmkl_def -Wl,--end-group -lpthread"
  - MKL version 10.3 or newer
    ./configure --with-blas="-Wl,--start-group -L$MKLROOT/lib/intel64 -lmkl_intel_lp64 \
        -lmkl_sequential -lmkl_core -lmkl_avx -Wl,--end-group -lpthread"
  - Link flags of other MKL version refers to the online MKL link advisor
    http://software.intel.com/sites/products/mkl/


Known bugs
----------

* For gcc and MKL 10.3 (Intel Composer XE 2011), some spinor-GTO
  integrals which invokes zgemm are incorrect.
  Replacing the default link falg -lmkl_gf_lp64 to -lmkl_intel_lp64
  can solve the problem.

* "make check" may fail in the following tests

* "make check" may fail in the following tests
  - cint2e_sph
  - cint2e_ig1_sph
  - cint2e
  - cint2e_sa10sp1
  - cint2e_sa10sp1spsp2
  - cint2e_spgsp1
  - cint2e_g1spsp2
  - cint2e_spgsp1spsp2


